cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.GR 

This paper is about generating realistic images from scene graphs, which involves computer vision (CV) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. The proposed model uses a scene graph context network to improve image generation, which is a machine learning (ML) approach. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces novel evaluation metrics for this task, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and human perception. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper deals with object relationships and compositionality, which are related to graphics (GR) and geometric modeling. Therefore, cs.GR (Computer Graphics) is also a possible sub-category.
